  40,1,Šł§√Ę-Mń©m
  40,2,"The revelation of this Book is from God‚ÄĒthe Almighty, All-Knowing"
  40,3,"the Forgiver of sin and Accepter of repentance, the Severe in punishment, and Infinite in bounty. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. To Him ňĻaloneňļ is the final return"
  40,4,"None disputes the signs of God except the disbelievers, so do not be deceived by their prosperity throughout the land"
  40,5,"Before them, the people of Noah denied ňĻthe truthňļ, as did ňĻotherňļ enemy forces afterwards. Every community plotted against its prophet to seize him, and argued in falsehood, ňĻhopingňļ to discredit the truth with it. So I seized them. And how ňĻhorribleňļ was My punishment"
  40,6,And so your Lord‚Äôs decree has been proven true against the disbelievers‚ÄĒthat they will be the inmates of the Fire
  40,7,"Those ňĻangelsňļ who carry the Throne and those around it glorify the praises of their Lord, have faith in Him, and seek forgiveness for the believers, ňĻpraying:ňļ ‚ÄúOur Lord! You encompass everything in ňĻYourňļ mercy and knowledge. So forgive those who repent and follow Your Way, and protect them from the torment of the Hellfire"
  40,8,"Our Lord! Admit them into the Gardens of Eternity which You have promised them, along with the righteous among their parents, spouses, and descendants. You ňĻaloneňļ are truly the Almighty, All-Wise"
  40,9,And protect them from ňĻthe consequences of theirňļ evil deeds. For whoever You protect from the evil of their deeds on that Day will have been shown Your mercy. That is ňĻtrulyňļ the ultimate triumph.‚ÄĚ
  40,10,"Indeed, it will be announced to the disbelievers, ‚ÄúGod‚Äôs contempt for you‚ÄĒas you disbelieved when invited to belief‚ÄĒwas far worse than your contempt for one another ňĻTodayňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  40,11,"They will plead, ‚ÄúOur Lord! You made us lifeless twice, and gave us life twice.¬†Now we confess our sins. So is there any way out?‚ÄĚ"
  40,12,"ňĻThey will be told,ňļ ‚ÄúňĻNo!ňļ This is because when God alone was invoked, you ňĻstaunchlyňļ disbelieved. But when others were associated with Him ňĻin worshipňļ, you ňĻreadilyňļ believed. So ňĻTodayňļ judgment belongs to God ňĻaloneňļ‚ÄĒthe Most High, All-Great.‚ÄĚ"
  40,13,He is the One Who shows you His signs and sends down ňĻrain asňļ a provision for you from the sky. ňĻButňļ none will be mindful except those who turn ňĻto Himňļ
  40,14,"So call upon God with sincere devotion, even to the dismay of the disbelievers"
  40,15,"ňĻHe isňļ Highly Exalted in rank, Lord of the Throne. He sends down the revelation by His command to whoever He wills of His servants to warn ňĻallňļ of the Day of Meeting‚ÄĒ"
  40,16,"the Day all will appear ňĻbefore Godňļ. Nothing about them will be hidden from Him. ňĻHe will ask,ňļ ‚ÄúWho does all authority belong to this Day? To God‚ÄĒthe One, the Supreme"
  40,17,Today every soul will be rewarded for what it has done. No injustice Today! Surely God is swift in reckoning.‚ÄĚ
  40,18,"Warn them ňĻO Prophetňļ of the approaching Day when the hearts will jump into the throats, suppressing distress. The wrongdoers will have neither a close friend nor intercessor to be heard"
  40,19,God ňĻevenňļ knows the sly glances of the eyes and whatever the hearts conceal
  40,20,"And God judges with the truth, while those ňĻidolsňļ they invoke besides Him cannot judge at all. Indeed, God ňĻaloneňļ is the All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  40,21,"Have they not travelled throughout the land to see what was the end of those ňĻdestroyedňļ before them? They were far superior in might and ňĻricher inňļ monuments throughout the land. But God seized them for their sins, and they had no protector from God"
  40,22,"That was because their messengers used to come to them with clear proofs, but they persisted in disbelief. So God seized them. Surely He is All-Powerful, severe in punishment"
  40,23,"Indeed, We sent Moses with Our signs and compelling proof"
  40,24,"to Pharaoh, Ham√Ęn, and Korah. But they responded: ‚ÄúMagician! Total liar!‚ÄĚ"
  40,25,"Then, when he came to them with the truth from Us, they said, ‚ÄúKill the sons of those who believe with him and keep their women.‚ÄĚ But the plotting of the disbelievers was only in vain"
  40,26,"And Pharaoh said, ‚ÄúLet me kill Moses, and let him call upon his Lord! I truly fear that he may change your traditions or cause mischief in the land.‚ÄĚ"
  40,27,"Moses replied, ‚ÄúI seek refuge in my Lord and your Lord from every arrogant person who does not believe in the Day of Reckoning.‚ÄĚ"
  40,28,"A believing man from Pharaoh‚Äôs people, who was hiding his faith, argued, ‚ÄúWill you kill a man¬†ňĻonlyňļ for saying: ‚ÄėMy Lord is God,‚Äô while he has in fact come to you with clear proofs from your Lord? If he is a liar, it will be to his own loss. But if he is truthful, then you will be afflicted with some of what he is threatening you with. Surely God does not guide whoever is a transgressor, a total liar"
  40,29,"O my people! Authority belongs to you today, reigning supreme in the land. But who would help us against the torment of God, if it were to befall us?‚ÄĚ Pharaoh assured ňĻhis peopleňļ, ‚ÄúI am telling you only what I believe, and I am leading you only to the way of guidance.‚ÄĚ"
  40,30,"And the man who believed cautioned, ‚ÄúO my people! I truly fear for you the doom of ňĻearlierňļ enemy forces‚ÄĒ"
  40,31,"like the fate of the people of Noah, ‚Äô»ād, Tham√Ľd, and those after them. For God would never will to wrong ňĻHisňļ servants"
  40,32,O my people! I truly fear for you the Day all will be crying out ňĻto each otherňļ‚ÄĒ
  40,33,"the Day you will ňĻtry in vain toňļ turn your backs and run away, with no one to protect you from God. And whoever God leaves to stray will be left with no guide"
  40,34,"Joseph already came to you¬†earlier with clear proofs, yet you never ceased to doubt what he came to you with. When he died you said, ‚ÄėGod will never send a messenger after him.‚Äô This is how God leaves every transgressor and doubter to stray‚ÄĒ"
  40,35,those who dispute God‚Äôs signs with no proof given to them. How despicable is that for God and the believers! This is how God seals the heart of every arrogant tyrant.‚ÄĚ
  40,36,"Pharaoh ordered, ‚ÄúO Ham√Ęn! Build me a high tower so I may reach the pathways"
  40,37,"leading up to the heavens and look for the God of Moses, although I am sure he is a liar.‚ÄĚ¬†And so Pharaoh‚Äôs evil deeds were made so appealing to him that he was hindered from the ňĻRightňļ Way. But the plotting of Pharaoh was only in vain"
  40,38,"And the man who believed urged, ‚ÄúO my people! Follow me, ňĻandňļ I will lead you to the Way of Guidance"
  40,39,"O my people! This worldly life is only ňĻa fleetingňļ enjoyment, whereas the Hereafter is truly the home of settlement"
  40,40,"Whoever does an evil deed will only be paid back with its equivalent. And whoever does good, whether male or female, and is a believer, they will enter Paradise, where they will be provided for without limit"
  40,41,"O my people! How is it that I invite you to salvation, while you invite me to the Fire"
  40,42,"You invite me to disbelieve in God and associate with Him what I have no knowledge of, while I invite you to the Almighty, Most Forgiving"
  40,43,"There is no doubt that whatever ňĻidolsňļ you invite me to ňĻworshipňļ are not worthy to be invoked either in this world or the Hereafter.¬†ňĻUndoubtedly,ňļ our return is to God, and the transgressors will be the inmates of the Fire"
  40,44,"You will remember what I say to you, and I entrust my affairs to God. Surely God is All-Seeing of all ňĻHisňļ servants.‚ÄĚ"
  40,45,So God protected him from the evil of their schemes. And Pharaoh‚Äôs people were overwhelmed by an evil punishment
  40,46,"they are exposed to the Fire ňĻin their gravesňļ morning and evening. And on the Day the Hour will be established ňĻit will be saidňļ, ‚ÄúAdmit Pharaoh‚Äôs people into the harshest punishment ňĻof Hellňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  40,47,"ňĻConsider the Dayňļ when they will dispute in the Fire, and the lowly ňĻfollowersňļ will appeal to the arrogant ňĻleadersňļ, ‚ÄúWe were your ňĻdedicatedňļ followers, will you then shield us from a portion of the Fire?‚ÄĚ"
  40,48,"The arrogant will say, ‚ÄúWe are all in it! ňĻForňļ God has already passed judgment over ňĻHisňļ servants.‚ÄĚ"
  40,49,"And those in the Fire will cry out to the keepers of Hell,¬†‚ÄúPray to your Lord to lighten the torment for us ňĻevenňļ for one day!‚ÄĚ"
  40,50,"The keepers will reply, ‚ÄúDid your messengers not ňĻconstantlyňļ come to you with clear proofs?‚ÄĚ They will say, ‚ÄúYes ňĻthey didňļ.‚ÄĚ The keepers will say, ‚ÄúThen pray! Though the prayer of the disbelievers is only in vain.‚ÄĚ"
  40,51,"We certainly help Our messengers and the believers, ňĻbothňļ in this worldly life and on the Day the witnesses will stand forth ňĻfor testimonyňļ‚ÄĒ"
  40,52,"the Day the wrongdoers‚Äô excuses will be of no benefit to them. They will be condemned, and will have the worst outcome"
  40,53,"And indeed, We gave Moses ňĻtrueňļ guidance, and made the Children of Israel inherit the Scripture‚ÄĒ"
  40,54,a guide and a reminder to people of reason
  40,55,"So be patient ňĻO Prophetňļ, ňĻforňļ God‚Äôs promise is certainly true. Seek forgiveness for your shortcomings.¬†And glorify the praises of your Lord morning and evening"
  40,56,"Surely those who dispute God‚Äôs signs‚ÄĒwith no proof given to them‚ÄĒhave nothing in their hearts but greed for dominance, which they will never attain. So seek refuge in God. Indeed, He alone is the All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  40,57,"The creation of the heavens and the earth is certainly greater than the re-creation of humankind, but most people do not know"
  40,58,"Those blind ňĻto the truthňļ and those who can see are not equal, nor are those who believe and do good ňĻequalňļ to those who do evil. Yet you are hardly mindful"
  40,59,"The Hour is certainly coming, there is no doubt about it. But most people do not believe"
  40,60,"Your Lord has proclaimed, ‚ÄúCall upon Me, I will respond to you. Surely those who are too proud to worship Me will enter Hell, fully humbled.‚ÄĚ"
  40,61,"It is God Who has made the night for you to rest in and the day bright. Surely God is ever Bountiful to humanity, but most people are ungrateful"
  40,62,"That is God, your Lord, the Creator of all things. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. How can you then be deluded ňĻfrom the truthňļ"
  40,63,This is how those who used to reject God‚Äôs signs were ňĻalsoňļ deluded
  40,64,"It is God Who made the earth a place of settlement for you and the sky a canopy. He shaped you ňĻin the wombňļ, perfecting your form. And He has provided you with what is good and lawful. That is God‚ÄĒyour Lord. So Blessed is God, Lord of all worlds"
  40,65,"He is the Ever-Living. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. So call upon Him with sincere devotion, ňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúAll praise is for God‚ÄĒLord of all worlds.‚ÄĚ"
  40,66,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúI have been forbidden to worship those ňĻidolsňļ you worship besides God, since clear proofs have come to me from my Lord. And I have been commanded to ňĻfullyňļ submit to the Lord of all worlds.‚ÄĚ"
  40,67,"He is the One Who created you¬†from dust, then from a sperm-drop,¬†then ňĻdeveloped you intoňļ a clinging clot ňĻof bloodňļ,¬†then He brings you forth as infants, so that you may reach your prime, and become old‚ÄĒthough some of you ňĻmayňļ die sooner‚ÄĒreaching an appointed time, so perhaps you may understand ňĻGod‚Äôs powerňļ"
  40,68,"He is the One Who gives life and causes death. When He decrees a matter, He simply tells it, ‚ÄúBe!‚ÄĚ And it is"
  40,69,Have you not seen how those who dispute God‚Äôs signs are turned away
  40,70,ňĻThey areňļ the ones who reject this Book and all ňĻscripturesňļ We sent Our messengers with. So they will know ňĻthe consequencesňļ
  40,71,when shackles will be around their necks and chains ňĻon their legsňļ. They will be dragged
  40,72,"through boiling water, then burned in the Fire ňĻas fuelňļ"
  40,73,"Then they will be asked, ‚ÄúWhere are those ňĻidolsňļ you used to associate"
  40,74,"with God?‚ÄĚ They will cry, ‚ÄúThey have ňĻallňļ failed us. In fact, we did not invoke anything ňĻrealňļ before.‚ÄĚ This is how God leaves the disbelievers to stray"
  40,75,"ňĻThey will be told,ňļ ‚ÄúThis ňĻpunishmentňļ is for being prideful on earth unjustly and for acting arrogantly"
  40,76,"Enter the gates of Hell, to stay there forever. What an evil home for the arrogant!‚ÄĚ"
  40,77,"So be patient ňĻO Prophetňļ. Surely God‚Äôs promise is true. Whether We show you some of what We threaten them with, or cause you to die ňĻbefore thatňļ, to Us they will ňĻallňļ be returned"
  40,78,"We already sent messengers before you. We have told you the stories of some of them, while others We have not. It was not for any messenger to bring a sign without God‚Äôs permission. But when God‚Äôs decree comes, judgment will be passed with fairness, and the people of falsehood will then be in ňĻtotalňļ loss"
  40,79,It is God Who made cattle for you so that you may ride some and eat others
  40,80,"Also, you find in them ňĻotherňļ benefits.¬†And by means of them you may reach destinations you desire. And you are carried upon ňĻsome ofňļ them and upon ships"
  40,81,And He shows you His signs. Now which of God‚Äôs signs will you deny
  40,82,"Have they not travelled throughout the land to see what was the end of those who were ňĻdestroyedňļ before them? They were far superior in might and ňĻricher inňļ monuments throughout the land, but their ňĻworldlyňļ gains were of no benefit to them"
  40,83,"When their messengers came to them with clear proofs, they were prideful in whatever ňĻworldlyňļ knowledge they had,¬†and were ňĻultimatelyňļ overwhelmed by what they used to ridicule"
  40,84,"When they saw Our punishment, they cried, ‚ÄúňĻNowňļ we believe in God alone and reject what we had been associating with Him!‚ÄĚ"
  40,85,But their faith was of no benefit to them when they saw Our torment. This has ňĻalwaysňļ been God‚Äôs way ňĻof dealingňļ with His ňĻwickedňļ servants. Then and there the disbelievers were in ňĻtotalňļ loss